The Kenyan leg of the 2016 Joss Stone East African Tour was organized by Bad Mambo events company. The multi-platinum singer, songwriter who has been on a worldwide tour took Nairobi by storm and thrilled her fans.She was the headlining act at the concert held at Purdy Arms in Karen. Since April 2014 she has been to Morocco, Dubai, South Africa, Lesotho, Swaziland, Australia and New Zealand to name a few.The singer has released four albums since her debut in 2003 and has won many accolades during her colourful career including two Brit Awards and one Grammy and is one of the top five richest artists under 30 in the UK.Musician Tetu Shani.Joss Stone on stage.Music enthusiasts at the concert.Photos/Moses Mwangi